,"renderedWidth":10,"renderedHeight":10,"naturalWidth":10,"naturalHeight":10,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"GOOD","altReason":"present, no red flags","bytes":232},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/icon_out.png","alt":"External Web Site Icon","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":10,"renderedHeight":10,"naturalWidth":10,"naturalHeight":10,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"GOOD","altReason":"present, no red flags","bytes":232},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/figures/m6125a3f1.gif","alt":"The figure shows the percentage of children aged <6 years participating in an immunization information system (IIS), in five cities in the United States, and the District of Columbia during 2010. Nationally, 18.8 million U.S. children aged <6 years (82%) participated in an IIS in 2010. Child participation in IIS has increased steadily, from 63% in 2006 to 82% in 2010, with an average 4.8 percentage point increase each year. Of the 54 grantees with available data in 2010, 24 (44%) reported that >95% of children aged <6 years in their geographic area par¬ticipated in their IIS. An additional 14 (26%) grantees reported child participation rates ranging from 80% to 94%.","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":524,"renderedHeight":380,"naturalWidth":524,"naturalHeight":380,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"TOO_LONG","altReason":"alt text is 674 characters — consider a caption or description","bytes":24227},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/mmwr/preview/mmwrhtml/figures/m6125a3f2.gif","alt":"The figure above shows the number of public and private vaccination provider sites enrolled and participating in an immunization information system, by year, in the United States during 2006-2010. From 2006 through 2010, 49 grantees (excluding Alaska, Georgia, Hawaii, Kentucky, Massachusetts, New Hampshire, and South Carolina) reported data each year. Among grantees with available data, the number of participating public provider sites increased from a low of 6,745 in 2006 to a high of 11,536 in 2010; private provider site participation also increased annually during the period, from 27,894 to 36,512.","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":520,"renderedHeight":340,"naturalWidth":520,"naturalHeight":340,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"TOO_LONG","altReason":"alt text is 608 characters — consider a caption or description","bytes":14669},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/icon_pdf.gif","alt":"Adobe PDF file","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":16,"renderedHeight":16,"naturalWidth":16,"naturalHeight":16,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"GOOD","altReason":"present, no red flags","bytes":6058},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/icon_word.gif","alt":"Microsoft Word file","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":16,"renderedHeight":16,"naturalWidth":16,"naturalHeight":16,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"GOOD","altReason":"present, no red flags","bytes":1087},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/icon_excel.gif","alt":"Microsoft Excel file","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":16,"renderedHeight":16,"naturalWidth":16,"naturalHeight":16,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"GOOD","altReason":"present, no red flags","bytes":644},{"src":"https://www.cdc.gov/TemplatePackage/images/icon_ppt.gif","alt":"Microsoft PowerPoint file","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":16,"renderedHeight":16,"natu